org.gradoop.flink.model.api.functions

Interface AggregateFunction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Average, EdgeAggregateFunction, Max, Min, Or, Sum, VertexAggregateFunction
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AggregateListOfWccEdges, AggregateListOfWccVertices, AverageEdgeProperty, AverageProperty, AverageVertexProperty, BaseAggregateFunction, Count, EdgeCount, HasEdgeLabel, HasLabel, HasVertexLabel, LabelSpecificAggregatorWrapper, MaxEdgeProperty, MaxProperty, MaxVertexProperty, MinEdgeProperty, MinProperty, MinVertexProperty, SumEdgeProperty, SumProperty, SumVertexProperty, UnlabeledGroupAggregatorWrapper, VertexCount

    public interface AggregateFunction
extends Serializable
    Describes an aggregate function as input for the Aggregation operator.

      • postAggregate

        default PropertyValue postAggregate(PropertyValue result)
        Compute the final result after the aggregation step was completed. This method may be implemented if the aggregate function uses some internal aggregate value not equal to the result.
        The default implementation of this method does nothing, it returns the result unchanged.
        This method will not be called when the aggregate value is null.
        Parameters:
        result - The result of the aggregation step.
        Returns:
        The final result, computed from the previous result in a post-processing step.

        Parameters:

        aggregate - aggregation result
        Returns:
        aggregated element
